Bibliographic References: GRFP, IIIA/3, pi. 34 c; BdA 43, 1958, p. 60, fig. 27; Italy's Life, no. 26, ill. on p. 103; PAd p. 13, no. A 202.
Imagery Description: Grey mullet, striped bream, dogfish and squid, with four small fish and two prawns. Rim: ivy.
Additional Notes: From the same tomb came the Orestes at Delphi squat lekythos (no. 142) and a stemless cup (no. 158) attributed to Asteas.
